<item>
            <title>[SOLR-17761] &quot;Global&quot; Circuit Breakers can trigger ConcurrentModificationException on Solr startup</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-17761</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;On startup, each Solr process will attempt to load each of the cores that it hosts (potentially in parallel).  Each core gets its own &quot;CircuitBreakerRegistry&quot;.  And on creation, these registries attempt to initialize some static state representing any global circuit-breakers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This can lead to a race where multiple loading cores attempt to modify the same static state, resulting in a ConcurrentModificationException.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should either have CircuitBreakerRegistry use a ConcurrentHashMap, or put some other locking in place to make the global CB state more resilient to races.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
